text: 180px Leticia Teleguario is a Kaqchikel politician and Indigenous rights activist. She served as Guatemala's Minister of Labor and Social Welfare between 14 January 2016 until 18 September 2018 under the government of Jimmy Morales. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Women government ministers of Guatemala Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Maya people
